 ('69', '69', 'en_us', 'Welcome', '<p>Mi aptent suspendisse sociis augue pretium eleifend ante suspendisse ad condimentum a a scelerisque a sem tempor tristique vestibulum ultrices lectus consectetur potenti fusce ipsum parturient fermentum.Tincidunt aliquet tellus urna pretium a mus quis adipiscing a a porta eget aliquet ullamcorper mollis leo. Natoque class a a tellus condimentum purus curabitur a fusce arcu congue conubia mus natoque at.</p>', 'Welcome to our little church', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Welcome to the Church of the Transfiguration, also known affectionately as The Little Church Around the Corner.\n  </p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-08-26 11:22:17', '2017-09-24 22:44:34', 'eb269d89-72b0-4fc3-adcc-78b124fcade3'),
 ('72', '76', 'en_us', 'The Rev. Ian Betts', '<p>The Rev. Deacon Ian Betts was born and raised in Canada to a Roman Catholic mother and a Protestant father so he had the best of both worlds as far as his religious backgrounds are concerned. He later discovered that his father\'s family was not only Protestant but Anglican so ultimately he has come back home to the Anglican Communion. Ian immigrated to the US in 1984 for a year to finish his dance training at the Martha Graham School of Contemporary Dance. He ended up staying to finish his dance education at the school for another 3 years and then began his performing career with one of his Graham teachers, Pearl Lang. Ian danced for Pearl for 17 years until she\'s closed her company.</p><p>In 1985, through a friend, Ian discovered the Episcopal Church of the Good Shepherd on East 31st St. After 9 years into his life at the parish, the Diaconate was brought to the Diocese of New York by Bishop Richard Grein and it became clear to him that he was called to the Diaconate. His Rector at the time highly recommended that he pursue this calling and in 1998 he was ordained Deacon. In 2002 Ians Rector retired so he moved to the Cathedral of Saint John the Divine for 8 years. When that term ended Bishop Andrew St. John invited Ian to join Transfiguration where he is now celebrating 8 years at this wonderful Parish.</p><p>Ian supports his ministry and life by working at a mid-town law firm as an administrative assistant. He has been working with lawyers since 1985 and grateful for their support of his extracurricular activities for over 32 year\\</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Deacon', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-08-28 15:15:46', '2017-09-26 10:38:31', '94ed6965-27de-4909-b641-a1de6d1885ae'),
 ('73', '78', 'en_us', 'The Rev. John David Van Dooren', '<p>Fr. John David van Dooren is a native of North Carolina, and was graduated from the University of North Carolina (1982) and the Virginia Theological Seminary (1987). His first field assignment was to an Anglo-Catholic parish, one of the only few in the the area. There Fr. van Dooren was introduced to a spirituality that would define his eventual priesthood and lead him to a lifelong commitment to urban ministry.</p>\n<p>After beginning his ordained life as chaplain and track and field coach at St. Stephens Episcopal School in Alexandria, VA (a happy period of life other than wrecking two school busses), Fr. van Dooren served as curate of All Souls Episcopal Church in Washington, DC. He then served as an assistant priest at St. Martins in the Field, Severna Park, MD, before being called back to All Souls as their sixth Rector. After 14 years as Rector, Fr. van Dooren accepted the call to the Church of the Atonement in Chicago, where he served as Rector for eleven and half years. Fr. van Dooren was elected the eighth rector of Transfiguration in early 2017. He has shared the past 30 years of life with Gary Norcross.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Rector', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-08-28 15:42:05', '2017-09-25 09:44:01', '6dc7c368-debc-4200-aef6-4db119142c16'),
