 ('323', '353', 'en_us', 'The Joseph Jefferson Window', NULL, 'The Joseph Jefferson Window at The Church of the Transfiguration', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The Joseph Jefferson window on the South wall of the main church building, memorializes the renowned actor who gave the Church of the Transfiguration its nickname, The Little Church Around the Corner. Jefferson is seen costumed as Rip Van Winkle, a role he was famous for. He is accompanying his deceased friend, George Holland to the church, where they are met by Jesus standing at the lychgate. The window is a gift of the Episcopal Actors Guild, and was installed in 1925.</p>\r\n<p></p>', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-14 18:20:39', '2017-09-14 18:21:01', '40fdc139-426f-47f4-8c7c-0ac30984678b'),
 ('325', '355', 'en_us', 'Liturgy', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>The Gospels speak of troubled people seeking to touch the hem of Christs garment, that they might be healed. Christs garment is no more, but before He left this earth He gave us what our prayerbook calls a foretaste of thy heavenly banquet  Holy Eucharist (or Communion or Mass), instituted at the Last Supper and celebrated every Sunday and weekday at The Church of The Transfiguration. Celebrate is the right word, because every Eucharist is a corporate giving of thanks to God for our many blessings.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, '2017-09-14 19:20:28', '2017-09-28 22:57:34', 'b74233dc-36fd-46fb-9dbe-f711c3e24e09'),
