 ('212', '355', '10', '1', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Liturgy\",\"slug\":\"liturgy\",\"postDate\":1505416800,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Among those blessings are the gift of the Eucharist itself and the opportunity it provides for healing, both individual and collective.&nbsp;&nbsp;At Transfiguration the Eucharistic<span class=\\\"il\\\">Liturgy<\\/span>&nbsp;(worship) offers a foundation for and pathway to deeper faith regardless of spiritual background or condition.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the words of the great Spiritual, \\u201clet us break bread together on our knees,\\u201d humbly asking God for forgiveness and for the strength and courage to do His will in our daily lives.<br><\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"251\"],\"12\":\"<p>The Gospels speak of troubled people seeking to touch the hem of Christ\\u2019s garment, that they might be healed.&nbsp;&nbsp;Christ\\u2019s garment is no more, but before He left this earth He gave us what our prayerbook calls \\u201ca foretaste of thy heavenly banquet\\u201d \\u2013 Holy Eucharist (or Communion or Mass), instituted at the Last Supper and celebrated every Sunday and weekday at The Church of The Transfiguration.&nbsp;&nbsp;\\u201cCelebrate\\u201d is the right word, because every Eucharist is a corporate giving of thanks to God for our many blessings.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-28 22:55:27', '2017-09-28 22:55:27', '550d8d8e-4761-4f13-8f6c-9fd4baa0dacb'),
